MENU DESCRIPTIONS
******************
FIRST OF ALL A RUN DOWN OF THE VARIOUS MENUS

ABOUT    = VERSION NUMBER, COPYRIGHTS, AUTHOR, UPDATES ECT
SLOADER  = WILL WRITE THE LOADER TO THE S DIR OF YOUR DISKS (DF0: ONLY)
QUIT     = END PROGRAM RETURN TO CLI OR WORKBENCH

EDIT	 = EDIT BOOT TEXT (13 LINES * 30 CHARACTERS MAX = 130 BYTES OF TEXT)
TEST	 = SEE WHAT BOOT WILL LOOK RIGHT (TEXT ALIGNMENT ECT)
WRITE	 = WILL WRITE A BOOT TO DF0: OR DF1: (V1.0 DF0: ONLY)

INSTRUCTIONS
*************
FOR MENU BOOT TO WORK YOU NEED THE FILE LOADER IN THE S DIR ELSE A NORMAL BOOT
WILL TAKE PLACE. 
THE PROGRAME WILL AUTOMATICALY PLACE THE FILE THERE IF YOU SELECT SLOADER FROM
THE MENU.
NEXT YOU HAVE TO ENSURE S/LOADER IS THE FIRST FILE IN YOUR STARTUP-SEQUENCE

EG 1
*****
S/LOADER	*1ST COMMAND OF YOUR START UP
LOADWB		*2ND COMMAND OF YOUR START UP
ENDCLI		*3RD COMMAND OF YOUR START UP ECT

FOR THE BOOT TO LOAD THE DESIRED FILES (EXECUTABLE FILES ONLY) THEY MUST BE
CALLED THE FOLLOWING

EG 2
*****
PRGA = F1 FROM THE MENU
PRGB = F2 FROM THE MENU
ECT......
PRGI = F9 FROM THE MENU
PRGJ = F10 FROM THE MENU

AND THEY MUST BE IN A DIRECTORY CALLED (BOOTFILES)
IF THEY ARE IN ANY OTHER DIRECTORY THEN THE BOOT FILE SELECTION WILL NOT WORK
AND A RETURN ERROR CODE WILL RESULT AND YOUR STARTUP-SEQUENCE WILL STOP!
IF ALL OF THE ABOVE IS DONE THEN YOU WILL HAVE NO TROUBLE IF YOU DO HAVE ANY
PROBLEMS MAKE SURE YOU HAVE FOLLOWED THE INSTRUCTIONS CORECTLY.
